<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[54793]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Ivo van Hove is back at the Grec festival with The Fountainhead]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[The Dutch director returns to Barcelona having delighted Barcelona audiences at the Grec festival 2013 with The Roman Tragedies by Shakespeare.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Ivo van Hove takes on the challenge of staging <i>The Fountainhead</i>, a novel by Ayn Rand. It is one of the most outstanding performances of  Grec 2014, the Barcelona summer festival. It is also the return of the Dutch director to Barcelona, after directing The Roman Tragedies by Shakespeare in 2013.</p>
<p>The leading player of the work is the architect, Howard Roark, who refuses to make concessions to his clients, even though it condemns him to failure and oblivion. It reflects on subjects such as art, creation and integrity.</p>
